This paper is primarily focused on image forensics, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential use of colorization to confound object recognition algorithms, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes detection methods for manipulated images, which could be relevant to the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis, which could be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
